sentence: Among the underlying components of the S&P 500 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Darden Restaurants, Inc. (Symbol: DRI), where a total of 25,697 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 2.6 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 138.1% of DRI's average daily trading volume over the past month of 1.9 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $85 strike call option expiring October 20, 2017 , with 10,354 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.0 million underlying shares of DRI.

Goldman Sachs Group Inc (Symbol: GS) options are showing a volume of 22,754 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 2.3 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 78.7% of GS's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 2.9 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $230 strike call option expiring September 22, 2017 , with 5,242 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 524,200 underlying shares of GS.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $92.50 strike put option expiring October 20, 2017 , with 15,836 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.6 million underlying shares of CRM.
